#entry(
  "Dassault Systèmes — 3DEXPERIENCE Platform Infrastructure & Cloud",
  [Infrastructure & Cybersecurity Apprentice],
  "Sept 2023 – Present",
  "Meudon, France",
  [
    - Developed a security hardening program for the On-Premise 3DEXPERIENCE Platform, for an energy customer, leveraging Rust's memory safety and concurrency features to build a health-checking tool that:
      - Verify secure configuration baselines (service states: TLS – versions and cipher suites – testing, sensitive HTTP headers check, HTTP Referrer filtering, HTTP methods management, and checking the absence of CVE-2020-1938 in TomEE AJP Listener).
      - Scan for known vulnerabilities in dependencies using the customer's database. 
      - Validate the presence and correctness of security-critical components. 
      - Generate reports with minimal runtime overhead.
    - Contributing to the _Customer Data Protection_ 3DS Eurowest initiative for helping a part of the geo to better manage sensitive customer data.
    - Installations and testing of OnPremise 3DEXPERIENCE Platform (23x, 24x, 25x, 26x), with any necessary Native Apps, on VM (Oracle Linux) for POC, and for partner and customer trainings. Dassault Systèmes Licensing Server installation for demonstrations (e.g, Airbus, Naval Group) or testing.
    - Assist the team to comply with ISO 2700(1,2,17,18) and NIS2 requirements.
    - Upgrading internal documentation explaining the Dassault Systèmes license's mechanism (OnPremise, and Cloud).
  ]
)
